GAM - testing effect of tmax anomaly on AGB growth

Code 
library(mgcv); library(data.table); library(gratia); library(marginaleffects); library(ggplot2); library(dplyr); library(tidyr); library(zoo); library(slider); library(regclass); library(effects)

load("../allplots_smooth_models_agb_growth.rda")

disturbed=merged[merged$Treatment=="disturbed",]
control=merged[merged$Treatment=="control",]

** model fits a separate smooth of Year for each subplot, but with a shared smoothing penalty (so all subplots borrow information from each other). ** AND tests whether the rate or shape of AGB change through time varies with temperature

**showing results for k=8 (k=5 gave similar results)

Code 
#hierarchical smoothing - fs (smooths are fitted simultaneously using a single likelihood) VS independent smoothing.

mod_fs1 <- gam(
  agb_growth ~ s(Year, subplot, bs = "fs", k = 8) + mean_z_tmax:Treatment, 
  data = merged,
  method = "REML"
)

gam.check(mod_fs1)
